<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="W" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Welkin" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Welkin,</orth> the sky: <bibl n="shak. ven 921" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 921</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. luc 116" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 116</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tmp 1.2.4" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. I, 2, 4</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wiv 1.3.101" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. I, 3, 101</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lll 1.1.221" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL I, 1, 221</bibl> (<emph>the --'s vicegerent,</emph> in Armado's letter). <bibl n="shak. lll 3.68.221" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 68</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lll 4.2.5" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 2, 5</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 3.2.356" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. III, 2, 356</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 3.2.47" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. Ind. 2, 47.</bibl> <bibl n="shak. tn 2.3.59" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. II, 3, 59</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tn 3.1.65" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 1, 65</bibl> <cit><quote>(out of my w., I might say 'element', but the word is overworn).</quote> <bibl n="shak. wt 1.2.136" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. I, 2, 136</bibl></cit> (<emph>look on me with your w. eye,</emph> == heavenly; German: <emph>mit deinem Himmelsauge,</emph> i. e. pure and innocent like heaven. According to others, == blue). <bibl n="shak. jn 5.2.172" default="NO" valid="yes">John V, 2, 172</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jn 5.5.2" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 5, 2</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 2.4.182" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B II, 4, 182</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 5.3.341" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 V, 3, 341</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 3.1.212" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. III, 1, 212</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 3.1.212" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. III, 1, 212</bibl> <bibl n="shak. tit 3.1.212" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. III, 1, 212</bibl>
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>